&lt;p&gt;1) We have royally screwed up the teaching of CSS.
2) Web devs are terrible at taking the time to learn how CSS works.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Itâ€™s probably both. And yes, some of the earlier stuff is not immediately intuitive: floats, vertical-align, etc. But it is understandable. You can make sense of this stuff.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Itâ€™s hard to see devs throwing their hands up in the airâ€¦ If this stuff is discouraging to you, please take some time to read up on it. Stop trying to hack through the brush alone. There are great resources available (p.s. Iâ€™m writing one!)&lt;/p&gt;
